WEBVTT

00:00.930 --> 00:05.956
Today's reading comes from the book of Matthew chapter 25 verses one through 13.

00:07.317 --> 00:13.104
At that time, the kingdom of heaven will be like 10 virgins who took their lamps and went out to meet the bridegroom.

00:14.085 --> 00:16.708
Five of them were foolish and five were wise.

00:17.549 --> 00:21.113
The foolish ones took their lamps but did not take any oil with them.

00:21.794 --> 00:25.798
The wise ones, however, took oil in jars along with their lamps.

00:26.639 --> 00:29.202
The bridegroom was a long time in coming.

00:29.442 --> 00:31.544
and they all became drowsy and fell asleep.

00:32.625 --> 00:37.189
At midnight, the cry rang out, here's the bridegroom, come out to meet him.

00:38.110 --> 00:40.693
Then all the virgins woke up and trimmed their lamps.

00:41.173 --> 00:44.296
The foolish ones said to the wise, give us some of your oil.

00:44.496 --> 00:45.597
Our lamps are going out.

00:46.318 --> 00:47.339
No, they replied.

00:47.900 --> 00:49.962
There may not be enough for the both of us and you.

00:49.982 --> 00:54.206
Instead, go to those who sell oil and buy some for yourselves.

00:54.986 --> 00:58.770
But while they were still on their way to buy oil, the bridegroom arrived.

00:59.042 --> 01:03.327
The virgins who were ready went in with him to the wedding banquet.

01:03.788 --> 01:04.649
The door was shut.

01:05.710 --> 01:07.732
Later, the others also came.

01:08.513 --> 01:11.417
Lord, Lord, they said, open the door for us.

01:12.097 --> 01:15.522
But he replied, truly, I tell you, I don't know you.

01:15.562 --> 01:20.267
Therefore, keep watch because you do not know the day or the hour.

01:21.008 --> 01:21.969
This is the word of the Lord.

01:25.273 --> 01:26.034
Please be seated.

01:29.666 --> 01:33.574
So today, we have a peculiar story.

01:33.734 --> 01:38.784
A wedding is late, but it's late because of the groom.

01:42.190 --> 01:43.593
Shocking, stunning.

01:44.755 --> 01:46.398
What's the latest wedding you've ever been to?

01:47.681 --> 01:50.126
Someone this morning shouted out, eight hours late.

01:51.268 --> 01:52.370
That's outrageous.

01:53.154 --> 01:55.918
I have the great privilege of attending many weddings.

01:55.958 --> 01:57.220
Many of you have attended many weddings.

01:57.320 --> 01:59.403
I've been the officiant at a wedding.

01:59.763 --> 02:04.349
The latest wedding I've ever officiated happened many years ago.

02:04.970 --> 02:08.375
It was a wedding out in BC, the interior of BC.

02:08.815 --> 02:11.259
I was invited to do this wedding for this amazing couple.

02:11.319 --> 02:19.350
I was excited, and we did it, and the bride, she said, we'll do it in my hometown, in the church I grew up in as a little kid.

02:19.370 --> 02:22.514
And it was a Mennonite church.

02:22.722 --> 02:24.404
The Mennonites are a lot of things.

02:24.905 --> 02:25.726
A lot of wonderful things.

02:25.746 --> 02:26.447
I love Mennonites.

02:28.350 --> 02:29.231
The rest of you do not.

02:31.074 --> 02:34.839
But the Mennonites, if they are one thing, they are frugal.

02:35.620 --> 02:36.842
And I love that about them.

02:37.563 --> 02:39.065
They know the value of a dollar.

02:39.906 --> 02:45.033
The only problem is their frugality shows up when they build churches.

02:47.757 --> 02:51.442
And in this church, the frugality meant there was no air conditioning.

02:52.130 --> 02:53.972
And it was 36 degrees Celsius.

02:56.255 --> 03:00.279
And the minutes were clicking by, click, click, click.

03:00.359 --> 03:01.681
And the ladies were wonderful.

03:01.981 --> 03:02.702
They looked great.

03:02.962 --> 03:05.986
They were in their summer dresses, cool, breezy.

03:06.366 --> 03:10.631
And the men were cursed with a suit.

03:11.992 --> 03:12.793
They were melting.

03:13.874 --> 03:15.436
And it became like a barn in there.

03:15.717 --> 03:17.278
So 15 minutes went by.

03:17.318 --> 03:18.700
I'm officiating.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.562
And I come out and I look at,

03:20.898 --> 03:26.725
hundreds of eyes staring out at me and they go, in their mind, I know they're saying, when does this start?

03:27.967 --> 03:29.969
And the information I had was, I don't know.

03:29.989 --> 03:32.292
We're waiting for the bride.

03:32.312 --> 03:35.836
15 minutes later, we're waiting for the bride.

03:35.856 --> 03:40.822
10 minutes later, I came on and said, fact check, we are not waiting for the bride.

03:41.303 --> 03:42.644
It is not the bride's fault.

03:44.667 --> 03:45.808
It's the florist's fault.

03:46.769 --> 03:47.911
She forgot the flowers.

03:48.311 --> 03:50.674
So eventually, an hour later,

03:51.330 --> 03:57.237
Everybody comes in, the bride comes in, half the men have melted into a puddle, but the rest of the wedding went off without a hitch.

03:59.941 --> 04:14.319
What's interesting in this text, Jesus, he's talking about a delayed wedding, and what he's doing is he's setting up his audience to be ready for this wedding that is a long time in the coming.

04:15.440 --> 04:19.986
In context, Jesus is talking about the end of all things, the end of reality,

04:20.994 --> 04:22.416
and the consummation of history.

04:22.716 --> 04:24.138
Where is everything heading?

04:26.261 --> 04:32.009
And then he gives this story to his innermost circle of followers to go, will you be ready?

04:33.011 --> 04:34.493
So that being said, we're gonna pray.

04:34.513 --> 04:37.918
Then we're gonna talk about how do we be ready for the end of history?

04:38.378 --> 04:39.380
How do you be ready?

04:40.461 --> 04:43.365
I invite you to pray with me and let's pray together.

04:47.932 --> 04:49.554
Father, you have

04:50.722 --> 05:02.059
unspeakable joy that you want to pour into the hearts of every man, every woman, every child in this room, watching online.

05:03.241 --> 05:07.808
You have a heart for every person in the city of Calgary, in our nation and the world.

05:09.951 --> 05:16.140
And yet you also give us this story that not everyone is ready for that great day.

05:18.303 --> 05:19.986
So today, Lord, there are people in this room

05:20.066 --> 05:24.052
who are exploring faith, exploring who you are today.

05:24.112 --> 05:27.517
In Jesus' name, would you reveal yourself to them by your grace?

05:28.878 --> 05:31.843
Would you help the people who are exploring to experience you and encounter you?

05:33.605 --> 05:39.353
God, I pray for those in this room who've become weary or embittered and who aren't living in your joy.

05:39.373 --> 05:41.056
They know you, but they've forgotten.

05:42.097 --> 05:43.759
Today, would you set people free?

05:45.502 --> 05:48.466
And Father, there are some in this room who are doing really well.

05:49.538 --> 05:51.180
And they have lots of your joy.

05:51.541 --> 05:55.686
Would you increase it even now in Jesus' name and for His sake?

05:55.707 --> 05:56.307
We pray all this.

05:56.888 --> 05:58.470
Amen.

05:58.490 --> 06:00.373
So if you got a Bible, we're going to be Matthew chapter 25.

06:00.393 --> 06:02.776
We're going to talk about preparing for His presence.

06:03.718 --> 06:10.227
And we're going to talk about, first of all, you will either live prepared or procrastinating.

06:10.467 --> 06:18.578
But I want to give us a little context because this text, Matthew 25, Jesus says the same message three times.

06:19.138 --> 06:22.342
Three times, it says be ready, be ready.

06:22.362 --> 06:23.524
Why does he do that?

06:25.146 --> 06:29.071
Because Jesus knows something about the human heart that you and I forget, and that's this.

06:29.552 --> 06:32.716
When we hear the same message over and over, so it's been a couple of weeks, guess what?

06:32.956 --> 06:34.278
Next week, be ready.

06:36.241 --> 06:40.006
But what can happen in a room like this is we kind of get sleepy.

06:40.607 --> 06:46.194
We get a little docile, we go, yeah, yeah, okay, Jesus said be ready, I'll be ready, and then we don't get ready.

06:49.794 --> 06:53.399
Like how many of us are feeling the rush of Christmas?

06:55.041 --> 06:58.365
You're feeling, oh, somebody raised hands, there's confession in the room, thank you.

06:59.307 --> 07:00.708
How many of you are like, I'm behind?

07:01.429 --> 07:03.112
What did Christmas sneak up on you?

07:04.574 --> 07:06.196
Just a surprise Christmas showed up?

07:07.477 --> 07:14.066
No, it's the very nature of humanity to put off what we should start today.

07:15.458 --> 07:22.466
And so Jesus, he's gonna give this message three times because apparently even, and he's teaching his innermost leaders.

07:23.687 --> 07:29.333
So what that means is for those of you who walked with Jesus for a long time, you're prone to forget too.

07:30.594 --> 07:31.475
I'm prone to forget.

07:32.657 --> 07:40.085
And so Jesus, he's going to set up this contrast that if you're ready, it's a wedding.

07:40.886 --> 07:43.469
Now for some of us, we're like, weddings are sort of perfunctory.

07:43.949 --> 07:44.850
They're not joyful.

07:45.186 --> 07:49.491
But in the ancient Near East, the wedding was the high point of society.

07:49.551 --> 07:50.312
It was a party.

07:50.452 --> 07:51.293
It was joy.

07:51.413 --> 07:52.214
It was music.

07:52.254 --> 07:53.456
It was dancing.

07:53.556 --> 07:58.181
It was food and feasting and family and procreation and sex and joy.

07:58.221 --> 07:58.902
It was everything.

08:05.090 --> 08:12.178
Or locked out in the dark where there's weeping and gnashing of teeth.

08:15.170 --> 08:21.637
See, the problem that I face as a communicator is we get three messages of the same thing in a row.

08:25.061 --> 08:29.185
And so we so easily become docile, sleepy, bored with it.

08:30.126 --> 08:40.818
But Jesus says, you have to understand this, because we do not know the time of the end.

08:41.186 --> 08:42.628
So Jesus, he's been talking.

08:42.688 --> 08:43.690
So here's the setup.

08:43.710 --> 08:45.273
Jesus, he's leaving Jerusalem.

08:45.293 --> 08:47.777
His disciples first followers point out the temple.

08:47.837 --> 08:49.139
He says, the temple's coming down.

08:49.199 --> 08:52.064
The disciples go, then this means a whole new world.

08:53.987 --> 08:55.449
When will the destruction of the temple be?

08:55.810 --> 08:56.891
When will your coming be?

08:57.011 --> 08:58.334
When will be the end of the age?

08:59.115 --> 09:01.639
And Jesus goes, many people will not be ready.

09:02.881 --> 09:03.782
So that's where we pick up.

09:04.644 --> 09:08.530
So he says this, at that time, the kingdom of heaven.

09:09.602 --> 09:13.047
will be like 10 virgins who took their lamps and went out to meet the bridegroom.

09:13.667 --> 09:15.710
Five of them were foolish and five were wise.

09:16.191 --> 09:20.316
The foolish ones took their lamps but did not take any oil with them.

09:20.997 --> 09:25.062
The wise ones, however, took oil in jars along with their lamps.

09:25.703 --> 09:30.249
The bridegroom was a long time incoming and they all became drowsy and fell asleep.

09:31.331 --> 09:31.932
So a couple of things.

09:31.992 --> 09:34.795
Jesus talking about the wrapping up of history.

09:35.496 --> 09:36.818
The final chapter

09:37.282 --> 09:42.668
that leads into the next amazing book, and he talks about the kingdom of heaven.

09:42.688 --> 09:53.340
The problem is when Jesus talks about the kingdom of heaven, most of us, when we think of heaven, the kingdom of heaven, we think of a spiritual world, of spiritual things.

09:55.843 --> 10:01.809
Pie in the sky, when you die, buy and buy.

10:05.233 --> 10:05.874
But we do.

10:08.738 --> 10:12.082
We do a unique thing when we think of the kingdom of God.

10:12.102 --> 10:16.107
We just transform it into this concept.

10:17.428 --> 10:25.578
But for the first followers of Jesus, when they thought of the kingdom of God, they thought the world being put back into order.

10:27.140 --> 10:31.865
The kingdom of God is actually the world, the way it would look if God was in charge.

10:35.169 --> 10:35.890
So for them,

10:36.482 --> 10:44.633
Heaven was earthy, it was the best food, the best feast, the best roads, the best system of government, because God would be king.

10:44.693 --> 10:53.205
It was an earthy reality, and the Christian view of the new earth of heaven is that.

10:55.308 --> 11:03.058
So somehow we got hypnotized, tricked into thinking that spiritual things are not physical things.

11:03.746 --> 11:12.778
In fact, the Bible's so serious about this that when it talks about what happens when you die, if you are in Christ, if you're united to Jesus, they go, you get a whole new body.

11:16.062 --> 11:20.427
For some of us, we should go, whoo, thank you.

11:20.447 --> 11:21.649
I could use a new body.

11:22.730 --> 11:23.792
I feel that even now.

11:24.753 --> 11:28.818
Those of you who are young in the room, you'll find out the rest of us now.

11:29.346 --> 11:30.567
Why would you need a new body?

11:30.587 --> 11:35.433
Because you're going to walk and you're going to hug and you're going to embrace and you're going to eat and feast.

11:35.994 --> 11:39.037
This is the kingdom of God.

11:41.860 --> 11:49.650
It also means the reason why this teaching about the kingdom of God affecting like earthy reality is this.

11:50.390 --> 11:53.554
It means that when you become a Christian, you just don't say a prayer.

11:54.306 --> 11:59.272
Let's get out a jail free card or life insurance for a good eternity after that.

11:59.732 --> 12:05.919
What you are saying is this, you are saying to become a Christian, you are saying Jesus is King.

12:05.939 --> 12:08.182
He's in charge.

12:09.683 --> 12:15.290
And then your life begins to come into alignment with his desires.

12:17.072 --> 12:18.994
And then your life has all kinds of meaning.

12:20.450 --> 12:30.804
Because then your life becomes a little showcase, broken, messed up, but a little showcase of what God is like and what it's like to live with him.

12:30.824 --> 12:35.290
And you, which is crazy, because you're unique.

12:36.392 --> 12:37.674
So your life matters.

12:37.734 --> 12:41.279
So Jesus says, we must be ready for the kingdom.

12:41.299 --> 12:44.723
And the way we get ready is we come into alignment with the king now.

12:46.426 --> 12:46.706
Okay.

12:47.714 --> 12:51.718
So he carries on, says the kingdom of heaven will be like 10 virgins or bridesmaids.

12:52.919 --> 12:57.664
So in the ancient Near East, weddings had three stages.

12:58.565 --> 12:59.726
There was the betrothal.

13:00.487 --> 13:09.035
So what would happen at the betrothal is the families would come together, the bride and groom would meet each other, the parents would meet, and then there would actually be what's called the bride price.

13:10.117 --> 13:12.179
And the bride price had to be paid.

13:13.400 --> 13:15.602
Now sometimes we think that's just because of

13:15.970 --> 13:20.376
a patriarchal system that existed, but it is actually far deeper than that.

13:21.998 --> 13:28.708
In the ancient world, if you had a daughter and your daughter lived with her family, she would do labor.

13:28.748 --> 13:31.532
She brought great value to the family.

13:33.254 --> 13:38.782
If you look in the Old Testament in the book of Genesis, there's this woman named Rachel, who marries this guy named Jacob.

13:38.922 --> 13:40.144
Rachel was a shepherdess.

13:40.925 --> 13:41.906
She did labor.

13:42.562 --> 13:46.408
So when a woman left her family, it left a financial hole.

13:46.448 --> 13:49.253
So the bride price helped to fill that.

13:50.655 --> 13:52.599
So there's a great bride price paid.

13:52.639 --> 13:57.567
Then, for many months, the groom would go home.

13:58.729 --> 14:00.171
And he'd go back to his father's house.

14:00.752 --> 14:06.802
And in his father's house, his job was to prepare a room, a place,

14:06.946 --> 14:10.370
where him and his bride would be together, where they would live together.

14:10.850 --> 14:14.794
And he would prep and work and build and fashion the room, and it would be beautiful.

14:15.976 --> 14:18.338
He would go away to prepare a place for his bride.

14:19.980 --> 14:30.231
And then, and then, at just the right time, the father would come in, and when it was all done, he'd say, it's ready.

14:31.312 --> 14:33.514
Go get her, go.

14:33.535 --> 14:36.818
And then they'd go usually in the evening, early evening,

14:36.898 --> 14:37.819
Not midnight.

14:40.604 --> 14:49.838
The groom and his groomsmen would come to the bride who would be waiting with her bridesmaids and then they would go back home and they'd be together forever.

14:51.420 --> 14:56.629
By the way, when Jesus uses language, Jesus, actually for the church, he calls the church his bride.

14:57.129 --> 14:57.630
Why?

14:58.491 --> 15:03.239
Because on the cross, Jesus Christ paid the price for his bride the church.

15:03.559 --> 15:05.362
Jesus bought you.

15:06.562 --> 15:07.163
He bought you.

15:07.703 --> 15:13.430
He paid all of your debt and bought you out of the kingdom of darkness, into the kingdom of light.

15:13.711 --> 15:14.932
And then Jesus went away.

15:14.952 --> 15:17.636
He went away.

15:17.696 --> 15:25.325
And this is one of the great polemics attacks on Christian faith today.

15:25.345 --> 15:29.490
A lot of people go, hey, how can you believe all this stuff?

15:29.762 --> 15:33.567
That's 2,000 years old, 2,000 years, 2,000.

15:33.587 --> 15:36.912
And Jesus is coming back 2,000 years.

15:39.735 --> 15:41.538
And you can't possibly believe this.

15:41.838 --> 15:43.180
It's been so long.

15:44.101 --> 15:46.304
If it was real, it would have happened already.

15:46.324 --> 15:49.008
A lot of Calgarians think that.

15:49.028 --> 15:50.289
A lot of Canadians think that.

15:50.990 --> 15:53.774
Maybe some of you in the room are going, yeah, that's a good point.

15:55.356 --> 15:59.762
What's interesting is this thought, this argument is not unique at all.

16:01.538 --> 16:10.368
In fact, it was so common that about 30 years after the life, death, and resurrection of Jesus, Peter, the right-hand leader, answers this objection in a letter.

16:11.609 --> 16:15.133
In second Peter, chapter three, it'll be on this screen.

16:15.794 --> 16:20.018
He's talking about people who are mocking the church, mocking people who believe this.

16:21.119 --> 16:27.186
And here's what he says, they will say, where is this coming, he promised?

16:27.490 --> 16:31.955
Ever since our ancestors died, everything goes on as it has since the beginning of creation.

